msItem.note:
Fourteen of the common prologues to the Pauline Epistles, all corresponding to the list in Ker, MMBL i. 97. Authors and Stegmüller, Bibl., numbers are as follows: 
(a) 677, Marcion, Romans;

(b) 685, Petrus Lombardus, 1 Cor.;

(c) 699, Petrus Lombardus, 2 Cor.;

(d) 707, Marcion, Gal.;

(e) 715, Marcion, Eph.;

(f) 728, Marcion, Philipp.;

(g) 736, Marcion, Col.;

(h) 747, Marcion, 1 Thess.;

(i) 752, Marcion, 2 Thess.;

(j) 765, Petrus Lombardus, 1 Tim., (‘scribens ei a Laodicia’);

(k) 772, Marcion, 2 Tim.;

(l) 780, Petrus Lombardus, Titus;

(m) 783, Marcion, Philemon;

(n) 793, Petrus Lombardus, Hebrews.
